					<h1>Technical Specification for the Simple and Extensible Sampling Tool Challenge</h1>

<h2>Background</h2>
<p>The Department of Health and Human Services, Office of Inspector General, is hosting a competition to create the foundation for an upgraded version of its statistical sampling tool. Previous versions of this tool have been leveraged to support billions of dollars in audit recoveries and findings. The tool is used by both government agencies and hospitals across the country.</p>
<p>The present website contains the technical documents required to complete the challenge. For more details on the competition itself please refer to <a href="https://www.challenge.gov/challenge/Statistical-Software-for-Healthcare-Oversight/">https://www.challenge.gov/challenge/Statistical-Software-for-Healthcare-Oversight/</a>. The official announcement for the challenge can be found in the <a href="https://www.gpo.gov/fdsys/pkg/FR-2016-09-29/pdf/2016-23124.pdf">Federal Register</a>.</p>

<h2>Technical Specifications</h2>
<p>The current version of the OIG sampling software and the associated help guides can be found at <a href="http://www.oig.hhs.gov/compliance/rat-stats/index.asp">http://www.oig.hhs.gov/compliance/rat-stats/index.asp</a>.  The competition requires the replication of 4 target functions: Single Stage Random Numbers, Unrestricted Attribute Appraisal, Unrestricted Variable Appraisal, and Stratified Variable Appraisal. The below table contains links to the technical details for the operation of the four functions. It also contains 10 example test cases. </p>

